The snacks in the white packs are called "otsumami", they are "beer" companion snacks. They have strong flavors as they get dulled out by drinking at the same time.

Here are EXPLANATIONS OF ALL THE PRODUCTS in the video and their time stamps from a random Japanese.This comment literally took hours to make lol 
1:53 Pizza Bun -  I’m assuming Felix went to LAWSON, and I don’t really recall what their pizza buns taste like. But I think convenience store hot foods are always good in general and enjoyable to everybody if you don’t mind eating meat. I think “Ann-man(Red bean paste buns)”might be vegetarian…but please check before eating to be sure. Many of us love eating convenience store buns in winter. Also for LAWSON hot foods, Karage-kun(Fried chicken meatballs) series is my favorite.
 CRUNKY - Pews kind of explained all, it’s chocolate with mini dotty puffs in it and has crispy and chocolate texture.
 ど太い小枝（dobutoi koeda）- Never tried or seen this particular one so I guess it’s brand new. This one seems to be the experimenting version of “小枝Koeda” a good old famous chocolate snack meaning “Twigs” lol. “ど太い” means “ tremendously thick” so I guess they kind of made a chocolate branch there. 
 焼きそばパン(yakisoba-pan) - This is classic snack food. It’s almost like onigiri(not as traditional but as common). I think it appears a lot in school set anime too.  Its basically stir fried sauce noodles between bread. It’s high in calories but you can’t resist eating it once in a while…
 チョコボール（Choco-balls）- This is classic and veery famous. Especially the TV commercial song and the character Kyoro-chan. I personally don’t like peanuts too, so never liked them…so thank you Felix.
 ビッグカツ（Big Katsu）- “Katsu” originally means “cutlet”. Generally pork cutlet. This is a snack trying to imitate pork cutlet using thin paper like dried fish meat and the bread crumb out layer. I had a phase in junior high eating this everyday …it’s not that bad, though it’s not that big either…

（the rest follows in the reply of this comment）
